ko-testkit for conventional actor unit tests, it could add coverage that's not needed for the actor artifact. I should also mention the Java serializer property configuration: if testing JavaSerialization, it's necessary to set \\\"pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization=on\\\" in the ActorSystem config instead of in environment or system properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is needed for meaningful pekko-actor_2.13 coverage; the observed failure is caused by tests using legacy TypedActor APIs that are absent from 2.0.0-M1.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system property setup is required. Generated tests should target APIs present in org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1, such as classic ActorSystem/Props actors, dispatchers, config, serialization, routing, DNS/settings, and coordinated shutdown. Avoid org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedActorExtension, and TypedProps because the resolved 2.0.0-M1 actor artifact no longer contains those legacy classes. If testing Java serialization specifically, configure the ActorSystem with pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization = on and warn-about-java-serializer-usage = off inside the test config.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko documentation commonly shows pekko-testkit as a test-scope companion for actor unit tests, but it is not required to exercise pekko-actor itself and should not be added unless the generated tests deliberately use testkit APIs.\",\n    \"Adding pekko-actor-typed_2.13 would test a different module; it is not needed for this org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13 issue.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ac74fd694f99c5016a427c998d188190942d6925f80220f8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1132, "output": 839, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28595, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782742155564, "responseId": "resp_02ac74fd694f99c5016a427c8c0fa881909e620e64ecb863f6"}}
